      "content": "It basically means your reasoning engine is being swapped out. Instead of you analyzing traffic patterns and predicting pedestrian behavior, the system will just use a simple sensor-response loop. If a sensor trips, the car brakes. It's much more predictable for the regulators, even if it's a lot less \"smart.\" The update will be pushed during the next scheduled maintenance window.",
